<span id="cb3-31"><a href="#cb3-31" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;error_lst_train&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> <span class="dv">1</span> <span class="op">-</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;accuracy_lst_train&#39;</span>]</span>
<span id="cb3-32"><a href="#cb3-32" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;error_lst_test&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> <span class="dv">1</span> <span class="op">-</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;accuracy_lst_test&#39;</span>]</span>
<span id="cb3-33"><a href="#cb3-33" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-34"><a href="#cb3-34" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> <span class="co"># Step 4: Compute error_barrier for train and test sets.</span></span>
<span id="cb3-35"><a href="#cb3-35" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;error_barrier_train&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;error_lst_train&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: np.<span class="bu">max</span>(x))</span>
<span id="cb3-36"><a href="#cb3-36" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;error_barrier_test&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;error_lst_test&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: np.<span class="bu">max</span>(x))</span>
<span id="cb3-37"><a href="#cb3-37" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-38"><a href="#cb3-38" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;first_error_train&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;error_lst_train&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: x[<span class="dv">0</span>])</span>
<span id="cb3-39"><a href="#cb3-39" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;first_error_test&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;error_lst_test&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: x[<span class="dv">0</span>])</span>

<span id="cb3-42"><a href="#cb3-42" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;last_error_test&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;error_lst_test&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: x[<span class="op">-</span><span class="dv">1</span>])</span>

<span id="cb3-45"><a href="#cb3-45" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;last_accuracy_test&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;accuracy_lst_test&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: x[<span class="op">-</span><span class="dv">1</span>])</span>
<span id="cb3-46"><a href="#cb3-46" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-47"><a href="#cb3-47" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> <span class="co"># Step 5: Compute normalized columns.</span></span>
<span id="cb3-48"><a href="#cb3-48" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> <span class="kw">def</span> normalize_array(x, alpha):</span>
<span id="cb3-49"><a href="#cb3-49" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> <span class="cf">return</span> x <span class="op">-</span> ((<span class="dv">1</span> <span class="op">-</span> alpha) <span class="op">*</span> x[<span class="dv">0</span>] <span class="op">+</span> alpha <span class="op">*</span> x[<span class="op">-</span><span class="dv">1</span>])</span>
<span id="cb3-50"><a href="#cb3-50" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-51"><a href="#cb3-51" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> alpha_values <span class="op">=</span> np.linspace(<span class="dv">0</span>, <span class="dv">1</span>, <span class="dv">25</span>)</span>
<span id="cb3-52"><a href="#cb3-52" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>

<span id="cb3-54"><a href="#cb3-54" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;norm_loss_test&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df.<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> row: normalize_array(str_to_array(row[<span class="st">&#39;losses_test&#39;</span>]), alpha_values), axis<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">1</span>)</span>
<span id="cb3-55"><a href="#cb3-55" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;norm_error_train&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df.<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> row: normalize_array(row[<span class="st">&#39;error_lst_train&#39;</span>], alpha_values), axis<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">1</span>)</span>
<span id="cb3-56"><a href="#cb3-56" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;norm_error_test&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df.<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> row: normalize_array(row[<span class="st">&#39;error_lst_test&#39;</span>], alpha_values), axis<span class="op">=</span><span class="dv">1</span>)</span>
<span id="cb3-57"><a href="#cb3-57" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-58"><a href="#cb3-58" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>

<span id="cb3-60"><a href="#cb3-60" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;norm_loss_barrier_test&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;norm_loss_test&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: np.<span class="bu">max</span>((x)))</span>
<span id="cb3-61"><a href="#cb3-61" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;norm_error_barrier_train&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;norm_error_train&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: np.<span class="bu">max</span>(x))</span>
<span id="cb3-62"><a href="#cb3-62" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> df[<span class="st">&#39;norm_error_barrier_test&#39;</span>] <span class="op">=</span> df[<span class="st">&#39;norm_error_test&#39;</span>].<span class="bu">apply</span>(<span class="kw">lambda</span> x: np.<span class="bu">max</span>(x))</span>
<span id="cb3-63"><a href="#cb3-63" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> <span class="cf">return</span> df</span></code></pre></div>
